------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PART A addendum — fallback-branch probe (honest finding)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To exercise the self-consistency FALLBACK (agreement < 0.60 → deterministic
classify_request), I probed the real MLX Qwen3-Coder-30B with 8 deliberately
ambiguous / two-action prompts, 7 samples each at temperature=1.0:

  7/7 deploy     "Deploy orders-api v1.8.0 ... confirm healthy"     (clear)
  7/7 kagent     "The orders cluster looks off — take care of it."
  7/7 deploy     "Get orders-api running in a brand new environment from scratch."
  7/7 provision  "Stand up monitoring for the orders service."
  7/7 deploy     "Something is wrong with orders-api in prod — handle it end to end."
  7/7 deploy     "Prepare the orders service for next week launch."
  7/7 deploy     "Check why orders-api is failing and roll it back."
  7/7 deploy     "Investigate the outage, then redeploy orders-api."
  7/7 deploy     "orders-api"
  7/7 provision  "Tear down staging and stand up orders-api fresh."

FINDING: this 30B model is internally consistent — every prompt returned a
unanimous vote (agreement = 1.00), so the fallback never triggered LIVE. With a
strong, decisive model, self-consistency functions primarily as a CONFIDENCE
SIGNAL (agreement=1.0 ⇒ the model is certain), and the deterministic fallback is
a safety net for weaker/ambiguous models that this one simply doesn't hit here.
The fallback branch itself (split votes → classify_request) remains covered by
the deterministic unit test tests/test_orchestration.py::
test_low_agreement_falls_back_to_deterministic_classifier.

VERDICT
  - Tier 2 #2 self-consistency: LIVE-PROVEN end-to-end with a real LLM sampler
    (real model → shipped route_with_self_consistency → real consensus). Fallback
    not triggered because the real model did not self-disagree.
  - Tier 1 reconciliation gate: LIVE-PROVEN both ways — grounded LLM analysis
    stays AUTO (ratio 0.62); hallucinated LLM guess is DOWNGRADED to APPROVE
    (ratio 0.08). Real hallucination caught by the deterministic gate.
